						               													<description>From the Inside Cover:&amp;#10;&amp;#10;this is a set of variants and games based on Diplomacy, the popular game of international negotiation, intrigue, and warfare (voted Game of the Year in 1976 and 1977 by Games &amp;amp; Puzzles readers).  It is necessary to know how to play Diplomacy in order to use this booklet.  Many of the games also require use of a Diplomacy board and pieces.  Mapsheets are provided for others, but a set of pieces is still required.  In all cases all additional rules needed are included.  The games range from the abstract to World War II to &amp;quot;swords and sorcery&amp;quot;, some for fewer than seven players.  They are arranged in a progressive instructive format to enable inexperienced players to learn simple variants first and more complex ones later.  There are also special sections on two - and three - player Diplomacy.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Table of Contents :&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Part I Simple Variants&amp;#10;  Simple Variants using the Boxed Game Board&amp;#10;  1939 (World War II)*&amp;#10;  Colonization&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Part II Moderate Variants&amp;#10;  Holy Roman Empire&amp;#10;  The Struggle for Hegemony in Europe, 1689-1815*&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Part III Complex Variants&amp;#10;  1939 II*&amp;#10;  Realistic Variants&amp;#10;  The Song of the Night: Swords and Sorcery Diplomacy*&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Part IV Miscellaneous &amp;#10;  Two-Player Diplomacy&amp;#10;  Three-Player Diplomacy&amp;#10;  Compilation of Simple Variants&amp;#10;&amp;#10;3 11x17 mapsheets are included&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;     uses separate Mapsheet&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
